The New Nigeria Peoples Party (NNPP) has intensified its lobby of the military officers wives ahead of next month’s presidential election. The Federal Capital Territory (FCT) Women leader and head of Women Awareness and political Enlightenment, Hajiya Saudat Abdullahi, who stated this yesterday in Abuja when she met with the executives of Nobel Women comprising Nigeria Airforce and Army officer’s wives across the barracks. The meeting was about strategies,  synergies and Coordination of how to galvanise 10 million votes for the NNPP presidential candidate, Dr Muhammad Rabiu Musa Kwankwaso. Abdullahi, who met the women leaders in her office at the NNPP Presidential Campaign Office, in Abuja, said the NNPP is mobilising wives of military officers across the country to participate effectively in elections. She also added that the party is making inroads with galvanising youths to vote for the party. Abdullahi who charged women and youths to go and collect their PVCs added that it was essential to their clamour for a better Nigeria. She said, “We have been strategising daily on how to ensure that we garner enormous votes for the NNPP in the barracks across the country. These are Nigerians who also deserve to have a say in the quality of leadership that comes on board after next months election.” She added that NNPP has also have been mobilising the youths across the country. “We have met with a lot of youths across the nation and our target to get no less than 10 million votes is on course.” She assured the noble women that the party will do what it takes to mobilise them to get into the field and work for NNPP. She said, “Those in the barracks have been mobilised to go and collect their PVCs and they are ready to vote.” She added that Kwankwaso is a man of character and integrity, adding that his legacies and landmark achievements are worthy of emulation. 